{
  "texts": [
    "However, challenges persist in capturing contextual word relations within documents and avoiding oversmoothing effects.",
    "To solve the above problems, Text-level GCN 33 creates individual graphs for each input text, allowing the learning of text-level word interactions through a message-passing mechanism.",
    "While the GCN model is a special form of Laplacian smoothing to represent adjacent nodes 34, potentially resulting in feature over-smoothing with excessive convolutional layers, the CPG-like GCN 35 incorporates layers with pre-trained CodeBERT and hybrid neural network models.",
    "Propaganda detection at multiclass multilabel Multimodal learning has surfaced as a strategy for identifying propaganda tactics.",
    "For example, Vosoughi et al."
  ]
